<note id="fs-id1167794188673" class="checkpoint">
<exercise id="fs-id1167794188677">
<problem id="fs-id1167793944345">
<para id="fs-id1167793944347">Draw the radial field <m:math><m:mrow><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mtext>F</m:mtext></m:mstyle><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mspace width="0.1em"/><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mtext>i</m:mtext></m:mstyle><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mspace width="0.1em"/><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mtext>j</m:mtext></m:mstyle><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1167793925697"><para id="fs-id1167793925698"><newline/>
<media id="fs-id1167793925702" alt="A visual representation of the given radial field in a coordinate plane. The magnitudes increase further from the origin. The arrow seem to be stretching away from the origin in a rectangular shape.">
